ere `ALL` is actually a column name or alias that got anonymized, which would explain why the parser is confused about what comes after it.\n\nThe real question is whether we need to handle this edge case where `GROUP BY ALL col_37` appears in the anonymized corpus, even if it's not standard BigQuery syntax—it might be a quirk of how the original query was transformed during preprocessing. I'm realizing this `GROUP BY ALL col_37` pattern is tricky to parse without knowing the exact semantics—it could mean grouping by all non-aggregate columns, or it could be a different syntax entirely. Since this only affects 4 files and the fix isn't straightforward, I'll move on to tackle the COPY GRANTS issues with CREATE VIEW and the MATERIALIZED VIEW problems instead, which seem more tractable.\n\nNow I'm looking at the `COPY GRANTS (col_list) AS SELECT` pattern—the parser is expecting `AS` right after `COPY GRANTS` but finding a column list in parentheses instead. The fix is to allow an optional column list between `COPY GRANTS` and `AS` in MATERIALIZED VIEW statements. The other error with `CREATE VIEW name (col_list) COPY GRANTS AS SELECT` already works in my tests, so there might be something else causing those failures.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1357,"cache_read_input_tokens":123158,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1357},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c43ed8a1-1b85-4dfe-81fe-8f9500711026","uuid":"ad0abdb4-ea44-437a-890a-7c48ae54f2bb"}
