{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LcDgj5sAYbNPMKcviUKQDg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good - the COPY GRANTS files don't have ARRAY issues. So let me do BOTH fixes together:\n\n1. Fix `ARRAY(type)` in Snowflake dialect → fixes 3 files\n2. Fix `COPY GRANTS (col_list)` in MATERIALIZED VIEW → fixes 4 files\n\nTotal: 7 files fixed (potentially more if sqlglot files also benefit).\n\nLet me implement both fixes. Let me start with the simpler one:\n\n**Fix 1: ARRAY(type) for Snowflake**\n\n\nNow I'm modifying the parser to handle ARRAY with type parameters in Snowflake - when it encounters an opening parenthesis after ARRAY, it should parse the inner type and wrap it properly.\n\nFor the second fix, I'm adding logic to parse column lists that follow COPY GRANTS in CREATE MATERIALIZED VIEW statements when no columns were already defined.\n\nBut I realize the `columns` variable is immutable since it's bound with `let`, so I'd need to change it to `let mut` to reassign it later. Let me trace through how `columns` is used throughout the CREATE MATERIALIZED VIEW parsing to make sure this change won't break anything.\n\nLooking at the flow for `CREATE MATERIALIZED VIEW name COPY GRANTS (col_list) AS`, the column list gets parsed initially at line 4617 but returns empty because the next token is `COPY` instead of `(`. After we consume the COPY GRANTS keywords, we'd then need to parse the actual column list that follows. Rather than parsing it twice, I should check if there's a simpler way to handle this.\n\nThe cleanest approach is to make `columns` mutable and parse it again after handling COPY GRANTS if it's still empty and we encounter an opening parenthesis. This way, both Snowflake patterns work: columns before COPY GRANTS or columns after it.\n\nModifying the fix...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1525,"cache_read_input_tokens":143208,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1525},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c43ed8a1-1b85-4dfe-81fe-8f9500711026","uuid":"ad6e73ba-3cfd-4f19-8652-a7d5e3614e92"}
